    <li id="pearl_linear_2013">Pearl, Judea (May 29, 2013). “Linear Models: A Useful “Microscope” for Causal Analysis”. In: <em>Journal of Causal Inference</em> 1.1, pp. 155–170. issn: 2193-3685, 2193-3677. doi: 10.1515/jci-2013-0003. url: <a href="https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/jci-2013-0003/html">https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/jci-2013-0003/html</a> (visited on 03/16/2023).</li>
